result.execSummary:
The defendant Levi Ramone Dacorah Kearney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. records.addlTxt: Cases called: 14CF583, 14CM623, 14CM622 & 15CF176, Defendant Levi Ramone Dacorah Kearney in court with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over. Information filed, reading waived. Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant pled no contest to counts 1,3,4,5 in 14CF583 (ct. 2 read in and dismissed), Ct.1 in 14CM622, ct. 1 in 14CM623, ct. 1 in 15CF176 (cts. 2-4 read in and dismissed). Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence withheld in 14CF583, 14CM622 & 14CM623, defendant placed on 4 yrs. probation, conds. in all cases: Complete AODA and comply with all treatment recommendations. Review of cases to be done in six months. Submit DNA sample on the felony, pay surcharge, complete sex offender treatment and comply with registration. $75 restitution in 14CF583, pay in first six months, in 14CF583,  $543, $443, $443 costs, rest of cases $443 each count pled to, 60 days jail on ct. 3 in 14CF583 start June 29, 2015 at 7 p.m. Huber granted pursuant to WI. Stat. 303.08  In 15CF176, 30 days jail, consecutive, $443 costs, 60 days to pay or set up payment plan with Clerk of Court. Deferred Prosecution Agreement accepted in 14CF583 on count one.  Jail credit: 5 days in 14CF583, cash bond to be applied toward restitution, balance applied to 15CF176.
